In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2009 as National Cybersecurity Awareness Month. He acknowledges the increasing dependence on digital technologies and the growing threat of cyber attacks and loss of privacy. The President emphasizes the need for greater security of digital networks and infrastructures. He calls on individuals, businesses, and governments to work together to improve cybersecurity and protect sensitive information, e-commerce integrity, and digital infrastructures. The Department of Homeland Security (DHS) and the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) support and promote cybersecurity education, providing basic cybersecurity tips for computer users. The President highlights the importance of treating digital infrastructure as a strategic national asset and a national security priority. He urges the creation of a more secure America where technology can evolve in a protected and productive environment.